  "prompt": "Why does Obama say ISIL instead of ISIS?",
  "response": "During his presidency, Barack Obama referred to the terrorist group as \"ISIL\" (Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant) instead of \"ISIS\" (Islamic State of Iraq and Syria) because the term \"Levant\" more accurately reflects the group's broader regional ambitions. The Levant includes not only Iraq and Syria but also Lebanon, Jordan, and Israel/Palestine. Using \"ISIL\" emphasizes the group's goal to establish a caliphate across a wider area, which aligns with their stated objectives. Both terms, however, refer to the same organization.",
